Got to try the famous Maguro Brothers poke in Waikiki and it did not disappoint. The place is very small and easy to miss if it wasn’t for the crowd of people waiting outside for their food. Definitely plan to wait 20-30 mins in times that they are really busy! There is also no seating so it is literally a grab and go kind of place.  The quality of fish is so fresh and truly delicious. The best way in my opinion to order if it’s your first time is to do a 1/2 and 1/2 situation so you can try 2 things instead of one. I tried the mix maguro and the spicy poke and both were sooo good. My boyfriend tried the Hawaiian poke and he felt like it was good and very fresh. I had tried some other poke places in the area and this was one of my favorites.

Well, if you don't really care for chains.  Fortunately, I had tried Maguro Brothers at their Chinatown location a few years back and was glad they had a location within walking distance of our hotel.  The menu had expanded since I saw it, but the nice customer service and short time to get food after ordering was the same. I'm not sure if it was this shop, eating outside in the heat vs AC, a change in quality over the years, or just my perception from my first visit at the other location years ago, but the fish was alright not amazing. Better than some of the other food in the area, but it wouldn't be top of my list to return.  If you decide to go, be prepared to take to go or eat outside. Maguro is the Japanese word for blue-fin tuna. This restaurant mostly serves different cuts of raw tuna, plus a few other seafoods like octopus and salmon. Very high quality for very reasonable prices. Poke is very good, but the sashimi is even better and you won't find prices this low for this quality on the mainland USA or in Japan. Takeout only; there is no indoor seating, but people who want to eat their fish when it is freshly cut can sit on the window sill outside. Expect to wait to place your order and wait more for it to be freshly prepared for you. Ask the cashier for chopsticks. Maguro Brothers also has a small booth in Chinatown (lunch only).

It's very small and there isn't a place to sit at the restaurant but there is a food truck park about a block down with ample seating

Best poke, good rice, good fish, excellent flavours. The only reason why I knock off a star is because they substitute rice for greens for a dollar more... But the amount of greens absolutely do not justify the 1 dollar price increase. They need to add more veg in that, cucumbers, seaweed, carrots, w/e, just give me a reason to okay the price difference.
Excellent food, super friendly. Even made a custom order for me. Definitely will go back.
Awesome fresh poke and fresh sushi available.

Amazing amount of fresh poke and sashimi at a reasonable price.
Chirashi bowl and spicy mayo tuna was my favorite thing to get and couldn't stop coming back for more..

I expected this place to impress me more, but it just didn't. This is definitely a hole-in-the-wall, and looks like they've converted one of the apartments in that complex into what basically amounts to a food truck without mobile capability, so there's that. There isn't any place to sit and eat, either, so you'll need to take that into consideration. The actual poke that we got was pretty heavy on the mayo, when applicable, and wasn't the best tasting tuna, either. The owners are friendly, though.
Really fresh poke from a whole in the wall. Delicious. You have a few options for toppings and sauce for the poke bowl. Heads up that they only do takeout.

Best poke Bowl i ever had in my life !!! These brother rock the market. Best quality Tuna !!

Simply the freshest poke anywhere. My ahi melted in my mouth and after every bite I was saying "oh my god!" Walking around in Waikiki searching for poke that would give me a bit of local flavor, not touristy, not a chain. This place blew me away. I have never had poke so good. Should be the #1 place in Honolulu.  Thank you Maguro Brothers for doing Poke right!

Fresh but small portion and doesn't taste so much. I had poke bowl with hawaiian limo sauce and chirashi don (with few kinds of fish), both were too much rice compare to the portion of fish. Although it's named as poke bowl, but there are no extra features like green beans, dry onion, kimchi, etc... it was only just fish and thin sea weed and rice. It's quite disappointing if you expect the standard tasty big poke bowl here.  The service was good, but the quality was simply not what you can expect from all those 'best poke in hawaii' reviews... there are better ones with lower price for sure.
Best poke in Honolulu and served from an apartment window. Love it.

OMG! Those three letters sums up this place! Best poke I have ever had out of Japan!!!! The fish is fresh and SO delicious. This place is a window and you walk up to it and place your order to take away and attempt to savor the food.
A hole in the wall with the best fish in town.

The best #poke bowl and chu-toro #donburi we had in Oahu.  Passed by this block many times while looking for parking, but didn't notice it (especially in the evening) until I was really looking for it.  Thus putting up pictures from different angles to help you all nice folks find it easier :)

Take Out 이라는 제한과 스티로폼 용기 사용이라는 점을 제외하면 아주 괜찮습니다. 단, 치즈 케익은 일반 케익과 달라서 아이들이 좋아하지는 않았습니다..
Hawaiian Limu Poke bowl, please.

If you are in Waikiki and like Poke, you need to come to Maguro Bros. This is seriously the best Poke I have ever put in my mouth.  The Hawaiian Poke bowl has some seaweed and a bit of onion. It packs a little spice punch with a little heat and a lot of flavor. Absolutely delicious.  The fatty tuna is a huge portion for the price. The freshest you will find anywhere and absolutely amazing.  I may move here just for the Maguro Bros

I love their extra Uni option that you can add on to any sushi platter/bento!  I looove Uni and their Uni quality is waaaay better than most of those actual Sushi bar in town! and it's only $5 something extra too. it is usually crowded but it's sooo worth it:-)  They have 3 stalls for those who would like to come by cars too.  I don't really like Tako (octopus) or Ika(squid) but they are very willing to substitute with something else which is very nice of them too! (Because a lot of Sushi bars/Sushi restaurant won't do that) I am so glad to find this little sushi place in Waikiki!
Fabulous, fresh fish at a very reasonable price. Highly recommended!
We had spicy mayo poke and octopus poke and chirashi poke combo.  Fish was fresh, overall taste= Par
Fast, fresh and tasted great. Very easy to miss - it is literallt a hole in the wall
I ate chirashi with uni and ikura. very nice. I will definitely visit again.
A little hole in the wall that specialises in fresh poke. We tried the wasabi hamachi and the ahi and avo. Fresh and lively flavours.  You can add brown rice for $1. A great find
Seriously unbelievable sashimi for any price. Very fresh.

(Translated by Google) We went immediately by saying that the second store was opened following Chinatown. The taste is of course the best. Please check it before opening.  (Original) チャイナタウンに続き二号店を出されたと言う事で早速行きました。味は言うまでもなく最高です。営業時間が短いのでチェックしてから行って下さい。

This place was right behind my hotel and was probably the best place I ate the whole time I was in Honolulu.  It's easy to miss as it's just a window in the side of a building but they had the freshest most clean tasting fish I have had in quite some time.  The cost is extremely reasonable given the area and the portions are huge.  Service is fast and the staff was very nice.  It's take out only so make sure you have some place to eat nearby.  I highly recommend the Wasabi poke, it was delicious.
Their Toro is sooooo good !!!
Don't underestimate this little hole in the wall joint. It's got incredibly fresh and delicious poke and dons! Simple and packed filled with flavour. Amazing!

Between all the high rises and chain restaurants, this place feels like a little hidden gem. It's in fact almost hidden, as it's on a side street with not much signage, but well lit so it's hard to miss. Order from the uber-polite guy at the window and then hang out in the parking lot while you wait for your food.  For $30 we got three dishes - tacos, poke avo & ahi, and salmon sushi bowl. Everything was delicious! One taco was raw, one was cooked, but both came with super yummy toppings! The poke over rice and salmon over rice were both fresh and tasty. We plan on going back and we're not even here for that many days! Highly recommended!
Fast service, fantastic flavorful poke bowl (Hawaiian Limu), good selection when you're craving a poke or sushi bowl. Price was good. There's a bench right there to enjoy your meal.

Lovely little hole in the wall joint with smiling service and excellent food. No place to sit (emphasis on hole in the wall) but extremely quick service will have you running gleefully away with your food in no time.
(Translated by Google) Wasabi soy sauce was delicious. I was just good at sharing with two people.  (Original) わさび醤油美味しかったです。私は2人でシェアでちょうど良かったです。

Maybe it was just bad luck, but after I had the Spicy Mayo Ahi Poke, i was the whole night on the toilet throwing up.. Why I know it was this food? My friend ate the same like me for the last week, except of this one..
